267
00:10:59,476 --> 00:11:00,870
Dr. Karev can still operate.

268
00:11:00,894 --> 00:11:02,738
It just makes the surgery a
little bit more complicated.

269
00:11:02,762 --> 00:11:04,011
Wilson?

270
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:07,715
We'll attach sutures to both
ends of Lee's esophagus,

271
00:11:07,784 --> 00:11:10,051
threading them out
through incisions in his back.

272
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:12,270
Every day, we'll
pull on the sutures,

273
00:11:12,339 --> 00:11:15,073
thereby stretching the ends
inside toward each other

274
00:11:15,142 --> 00:11:17,575
in order to connect
them in a later surgery.

275
00:11:17,644 --> 00:11:19,778
However, for the
procedure to work,

276
00:11:19,846 --> 00:11:22,147
we'll need Lee to
remain extremely still,

277
00:11:22,215 --> 00:11:24,915
so we'll need to put him in
a medically induced coma.

278
00:11:24,984 --> 00:11:26,451
I'm sorry, but, Dr. Robbins,

279
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:27,813
why aren't you
doing the surgery?

280
00:11:27,837 --> 00:11:30,104
Dr. Karev is now the
attending on this case.

281
00:11:30,173 --> 00:11:33,169
I have recently started a new
specialty in a different department.

282
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:37,128
But I can assure you, I trained
Dr. Karev, and he is awesome.

283
00:11:37,197 --> 00:11:39,880
You have to put our
baby into a coma?

284
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:41,632
For how long?

285
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:44,202
This process could take weeks.

286
00:11:44,271 --> 00:11:46,148
There are other surgical
options I'd love to go over...

287
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:48,722
But this is the
best one for Lee.

288
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,231
Dr. Robbins, can
I see you outside?

289
00:11:52,678 --> 00:11:54,924
What was that? You're
just gonna make them worry.

290
00:11:54,948 --> 00:11:56,948
I was thinking of doing
a colonic interposition.

291
00:11:57,017 --> 00:11:59,283
I fix the kid in one surgery,
he can go home sooner.

292
00:11:59,352 --> 00:12:01,097
No, using the native
