00:30:36,401 --> 00:30:37,896
They're fluid-filled cysts.

745
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:40,320
Emily's arm injury ripped the
nerves from her spinal cord,

746
00:30:40,389 --> 00:30:42,656
causing her to
develop spinal epilepsy.

747
00:30:42,741 --> 00:30:44,908
Instead of having seizures,
she develops these...

748
00:30:44,976 --> 00:30:46,476
Shocks of pain.

749
00:30:46,545 --> 00:30:47,722
Is there any way to...

750
00:30:47,746 --> 00:30:48,923
Fix it? Yeah. It's risky.

751
00:30:48,947 --> 00:30:50,658
I have to burn the nerve
endings of her spine

752
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:52,811
to stop the communication
of the pain signals to her arm.

753
00:30:52,835 --> 00:30:54,501
Oh, can you do it?

754
00:30:55,671 --> 00:30:57,104
Are you kidding me?

755
00:30:58,456 --> 00:30:59,456
So...

756
00:30:59,525 --> 00:31:02,025
Addison Montgomery
with a toddler.

757
00:31:02,094 --> 00:31:03,576
Oh, yeah.

758
00:31:03,646 --> 00:31:06,196
Henry has completely destroyed
her white walls and carpets.

759
00:31:06,264 --> 00:31:07,647
He's currently into drawing

760
00:31:07,716 --> 00:31:10,817
and spilling and smearing.

761
00:31:10,886 --> 00:31:12,397
Yeah, well, looks
like we won't see her

762
00:31:12,421 --> 00:31:14,387
on the conference
circuit for a little while.

763
00:31:14,456 --> 00:31:15,983
Um, I didn't know that
you knew Addison, too.

764
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:17,824
Did you finish rounding?

765
00:31:17,893 --> 00:31:19,092
Yes.

766
00:31:19,161 --> 00:31:20,394
Um, yeah.

767
00:31:20,462 --> 00:31:21,539
I wanted to tell
you that Ms. Cain

768
00:31:21,563 --> 00:31:22,495
gave consent to
her valvuloplasty.

769
00:31:22,564 --> 00:31:23,708
Should I schedule it?

770
00:31:23,732 --> 00:31:24,814
Yeah. Day after next.

771
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:26,816
And you're leading
this one, Robbins.

772
00:31:26,885 --> 00:31:28,462
Graham will assist
and hold the needles.

773
00:31:28,486 --> 00:31:29,486
I'll observe.

774
00:31:29,538 --> 00:31:30,687
You be ready this time.

775
00:31:30,756 --> 00:31:32,796
Yes, ma'am.

776
00:31:35,511 --> 00:31:37,043
Did you need something else?

777
00:31:38,813 --> 00:31:40,046
N... No.

778
00:31:41,082 --> 00:31:42,115
Sorry.

779
00:31:43,018 --> 00:31:44,450
So, Henry...

780
00:31:44,519 --> 00:31:47,119
That's a cute name, though.
- It's cute.

781
00:31:47,639 --> 00:31:49,205
Hey, um, how's he doing?

782
00:31:49,274 --> 00:31:51,174
Can I see the most
recent gapogram?

783
00:31:51,243 --> 00:31:53,563
Uh, I'm not sure that I should.

784
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:57,147
I'm leaving, okay?

785
00:31:57,215 --> 00:32:00,716
It's your patient, your NICU,
your territory, so I'm gone.

786
00:32:04,890 --> 00:32:06,706
Okay, the cord's exposed.

787
00:32:06,775 --> 00:32:09,592
I'm about to send down
the radiofrequency probe.

788
00:32:09,661 --> 00:32:12,913
I never even thought to
look past the arm, and now...

789
00:32:12,981 --> 00:32:15,459
I may have blown her
chances at culinary school,

790
00:32:15,483 --> 00:32:17,764
gotten her hooked
on pain meds, to boot.

791
00:32:17,886 --> 00:32:19,086
It's not your fault.

792
00:32:19,154 --> 00:32:21,087
No, this problem
goes much deeper

793
00:32:21,173 --> 00:32:24,524
than anything you could have
seen or could have controlled.

794
00:32:24,593 --> 00:32:26,159
It's not your fault at all.

795
00:33:12,191 --> 00:33:13,911
Calliope. I... Shh.

796
00:33:15,894 --> 00:33:17,194
I need... I need to practice.

797
00:33:17,262 --> 00:33:18,494
No talking.

798
00:33:19,597 --> 00:33:20,763
Rules.

799
00:33:27,989 --> 00:33:29,789
Tomorrow's the last day.

800
00:33:31,059 --> 00:33:32,392
So? Close enough, right?

801
00:33:32,461 --> 00:33:33,759
Yeah.

802
00:33:33,828 --> 00:33:36,296
Oh, what if she makes
us start over again?

803
00:33:36,364 --> 00:33:38,176
So, what if we don't tell her?

804
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:39,499
Oh.

805
00:33:50,996 --> 00:33:52,607
Hey, um, I just got your page.

806
00:33:52,631 --> 00:33:54,642
I thought the Cain valvuloplasty
was scheduled for tomorrow.

807
00:33:54,666 --> 00:33:56,266
It was.

808
00:33:56,335 --> 00:33:57,796
Ultrasound showed
mild fetal hydrops.

809
00:33:57,820 --> 00:33:59,730
So, not only does it
have to happen today,

810
00:33:59,754 --> 00:34:01,994
it has to happen right now.

811
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:04,040
You ready?

812
00:34:07,495 --> 00:34:08,511
Ready.

813
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:09,929
Needle, please?

814
00:34:17,506 --> 00:34:18,555
Stop.

815
00:34:20,125 --> 00:34:21,257
What's wrong?

816
00:34:21,326 --> 00:34:22,871
I should be asking you that.

817
00:34:22,895 --> 00:34:24,393
I'm sorry. I don't follow.

818
00:34:24,462 --> 00:34:25,523
You hesitated.

819
00:34:25,547 --> 00:34:26,991
You steadied your
hand. I watched you.

820
00:34:27,015 --> 00:34:28,098
No, no, I'm fine.

821
00:34:28,167 --> 00:34:29,644
Are you nervous? No.

822
00:34:29,668 --> 00:34:31,284
I mean... Of course I am, but...

823
00:34:31,353 --> 00:34:33,819
Why? Why are you
nervous? Are you well-rested?

824
00:34:33,888 --> 00:34:35,121
Yes, Dr. Herman.

825
00:34:35,190 --> 00:34:36,417
But you're prepared, right?

826
00:34:36,441 --> 00:34:37,681
You studied the fetal echo,

827
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:39,037
you memorized the measurements,

828
00:34:39,061 --> 00:34:40,310
you practiced the angles?

829
00:34:40,378 --> 00:34:42,273
Do you know exactly
how far to insert the needle,

830
00:34:42,297 --> 00:34:44,592
at which point to deploy
the wire, inflate the balloon?

831
00:34:44,616 --> 00:34:46,544
I do. I think I... Do
you think, or you know?

832
00:34:46,568 --> 00:34:48,668
I know. I know. I know!

833
00:34:51,055 --> 00:34:52,800
Graham, trade
places with Robbins.

834
00:34:52,824 --> 00:34:54,157
Absolutely.

835
00:34:54,225 --> 00:34:56,359
Dr. Herman, I... It's fine.

836
00:34:56,427 --> 00:34:58,747
We've just lost
some valuable time.

837
00:35:08,089 --> 00:35:09,450
Hi. FEMALE DOCTOR: Hi.

838
00:35:09,474 --> 00:35:11,714
Where you been? FEMALE
DOCTOR: Vacation.

839
00:35:14,713 --> 00:35:16,879
Right in here is fine.

840
00:35:16,948 --> 00:35:18,247
Oh, hi.

841
00:35:20,736 --> 00:35:22,151
Let me just explain.

842
00:35:22,220 --> 00:35:23,731
Do you know how many
fetal surgeons there are

843
00:35:23,755 --> 00:35:25,266
west of the Mississippi River?

844
00:35:25,290 --> 00:35:27,335
Five. There are five of us.

845
00:35:27,359 --> 00:35:29,875
And I need a sixth,
Robbins, so I picked you.

846
00:35:29,944 --> 00:35:32,596
Out of everyone,
I handpicked you.

847
00:35:32,664 --> 00:35:34,945
And you are letting me down.

848
00:35:34,983 --> 00:35:36,594
I'm not just questioning
your abilities.

849
00:35:36,618 --> 00:35:38,368
Now I'm questioning mine.

850
00:35:38,436 --> 00:35:40,548
I thought you had something.

851
00:35:40,572 --> 00:35:42,150
I thought you were special.

852
00:35:42,174 --> 00:35:44,118
You're the chief
of pediatric surgery.

853
00:35:44,142 --> 00:35:45,453
You're a member of the board,

854
00:35:45,477 --> 00:35:46,954
well-respected among peers.

855
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:49,746
I thought you would be
better and in less time.

856
00:35:49,815 --> 00:35:52,615
But today? Today,
you embarrassed me.

857
00:35:52,684 --> 00:35:56,102
Today, you were unprepared
for the second time.

858
00:35:56,170 --> 00:35:58,048
So, I might have
to rethink this,

859
00:35:58,072 --> 00:36:00,350
because you might not
have what it takes here.

860
00:36:00,374 --> 00:36:01,819
I don't know what's
wrong with you.

861
00:36:01,843 --> 00:36:03,521
I don't know what kind
of demons you have.

862
00:36:03,545 --> 00:36:06,690
But I can tell you that you
are behind in this fellowship,

863
00:36:06,714 --> 00:36:08,993
and I don't have time
for you to catch up.

864
00:36:09,017 --> 00:36:12,886
I don't have time
for three strikes.

865
00:36:12,955 --> 00:36:15,721
Something like this
happens again, you're out.

866
00:36:26,317 --> 00:36:27,483
Any pain?

867
00:36:27,552 --> 00:36:28,651
No.

868
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:30,220
It's all gone.

869
00:36:30,288 --> 00:36:31,303
What about your arm?

870
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:32,972
Nothing.

871
00:36:35,143 --> 00:36:37,344
When my car hit that tree,

872
00:36:37,412 --> 00:36:39,892
the first thought that
came into my head was,

873
00:36:39,948 --> 00:36:43,649
"At least it's over.
No more pain."

874
00:36:43,718 --> 00:36:45,696
No more swallowing
a bunch of pills,

875
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:47,354
trying to make it stop,

876
00:36:47,422 --> 00:36:49,356
no more crying on my couch

877
00:36:49,424 --> 00:36:52,292
watching those stupid,
cheesy cooking shows,

878
00:36:52,361 --> 00:36:54,505
thinking about
food I'd never make.

879
00:36:54,529 --> 00:36:57,697
And, God, stop
feeling sorry for myself.

880
00:37:00,084 --> 00:37:01,901
Thank you.

881
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:07,006
I finally feel like I might
actually survive this.

882
00:37:16,184 --> 00:37:18,104
That's all you, you know.

883
00:37:20,038 --> 00:37:22,822
Well, he's got a tough
road ahead... Months of PT...

884
00:37:22,891 --> 00:37:25,007
But that graft should
last him for years.

885
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:26,954
Hopefully, this is the
beginning of the end for him.

886
00:37:26,978 --> 00:37:29,224
So, what about you?
It's day 30, isn't it?

887
00:37:29,248 --> 00:37:30,980
Hmm, it is.

888
00:37:31,583 --> 00:37:32,649
Day 30.

889
00:37:32,718 --> 00:37:36,336
Uh, I am... Weirdly nervous.

890
00:37:36,404 --> 00:37:39,405
I mean, I feel good,
but I... I don't know.

891
00:37:39,474 --> 00:37:41,157
It feels like coming
back from somewhere.

892
00:37:41,225 --> 00:37:42,937
Well, even though
the diet's over,

893
00:37:42,961 --> 00:37:45,256
I'm always up for
cheeseburgers and tequila.

894
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:46,312
Oh.

895
00:37:46,381 --> 00:37:48,164
Actual cheeseburgers.

896
00:37:49,684 --> 00:37:51,751
<i>Once the chaos subsides,</i>

897
00:37:51,819 --> 00:37:53,753
<i>we have to go back...</i>

898
00:37:55,407 --> 00:37:56,906
<i>Take another look.</i>

899
00:37:57,826 --> 00:37:59,859
<i>We have to ask ourselves,</i>

900
00:38:03,481 --> 00:38:05,848
<i>"Can this body be
put back together?"</i>

901
00:38:05,917 --> 00:38:08,595
We were able to put Lee's
esophagus back together,

902
00:38:08,619 --> 00:38:11,321
and I assure you,
it's stronger than ever.

903
00:38:11,389 --> 00:38:14,357
Thank you so much.

904
00:38:14,426 --> 00:38:19,162
<i>If we've done our
jobs right, it can.</i>

905
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:22,065
<i>We stop the bleeding.</i>

906
00:38:24,418 --> 00:38:28,171
<i>We sew up the damage.</i>

907
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:30,473
<i>We make the body whole again.</i>

908
00:38:38,300 --> 00:38:39,799
I understand why we did this.

909
00:38:39,867 --> 00:38:43,486
You know, it was to make
us stronger, to make us better.

910
00:38:43,554 --> 00:38:46,822
And it did. I mean, I
feel like it really did.

911
00:38:47,825 --> 00:38:49,559
It took a long time,

912
00:38:50,695 --> 00:38:52,695
and it was painful,
and it sucked,

913
00:38:52,764 --> 00:38:57,834
but we've come a long way.

914
00:38:57,903 --> 00:39:00,236
And I know that we
have further to go, but...

915
00:39:01,773 --> 00:39:03,556
I love you, Calliope.

916
00:39:03,625 --> 00:39:05,841
I love you.

917
00:39:07,011 --> 00:39:09,512
Life without you terrifies me.

918
00:39:09,581 --> 00:39:12,999
And the world is just
making less and less sense,

919
00:39:13,067 --> 00:39:15,435
and, like, I don't know what
I'm doing at work anymore,

920
00:39:15,504 --> 00:39:18,404
but the thing that I
need is my anchor.

921
00:39:18,473 --> 00:39:19,989
It's you.

922
00:39:20,058 --> 00:39:21,991
I need you.

923
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:25,511
And you're the only
thing that I will ever need.

924
00:39:25,580 --> 00:39:29,882
And I'm so glad that
this break is over.

925
00:39:46,434 --> 00:39:51,771
The last 30 days have
taught me so much.

926
00:39:53,774 --> 00:39:55,385
And all I wanted when
we first came here

927
00:39:55,409 --> 00:39:57,743
was to know that we
would leave together.

928
00:40:00,715 --> 00:40:02,893
But from the minute I
sat down, I could feel it.

929
00:40:02,917 --> 00:40:06,236
I felt like I was
gonna be suffocated.

930
00:40:14,595 --> 00:40:17,663
The last several weeks,

931
00:40:17,732 --> 00:40:20,599
I have laughed more,
I have done more,

932
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:24,037
I have enjoyed
myself more, than...

933
00:40:27,008 --> 00:40:28,974
And I finally feel free.

934
00:40:32,630 --> 00:40:34,964
And by being free,

935
00:40:35,033 --> 00:40:38,768
I can see now that
constantly trying to fix us

936
00:40:38,837 --> 00:40:41,637
is the thing that's
been killing me slowly.

937
00:40:45,376 --> 00:40:46,921
And I don't want
to do it anymore.

938
00:40:46,945 --> 00:40:49,712
I don't want to fix
it or fix us anymore.

939
00:40:53,050 --> 00:40:57,237
Maybe instead of loving
you so hard, I should...

940
00:40:58,172 --> 00:41:00,332
I should be myself for a while.

941
00:41:04,145 --> 00:41:06,713
I should love me,

942
00:41:06,781 --> 00:41:07,958
and you should love you,

943
00:41:07,982 --> 00:41:11,351
and together we love
Sofia, rather than...

944
00:41:20,428 --> 00:41:23,229
I want so much for you, Arizona.

945
00:41:24,432 --> 00:41:25,831
For both of us.

946
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:30,937
So much more than this.

947
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:35,973
More than being stuck with
someone who feels stuck.

948
00:41:40,648 --> 00:41:42,765
I want you to feel free, too.

949
00:41:51,759 --> 00:41:54,760
<i>But no matter how hard we try...</i>

950
00:42:03,955 --> 00:42:06,288
<i>we have to realize...</i>

951
00:42:13,665 --> 00:42:14,997
<i>some things...</i>

952
00:42:16,434 --> 00:42:18,234
<i>just can't be fixed.</i>
